Thienemann ( 1935 )
established the orthoclad genus Parorthocladius and treated the species Dactylocladius nudipennis as the type­species. According to
Cranston et al. (1983
, 1986 , 1989 ), the genus has a Holarctic and Afrotropical distribution. However, to date, the five described species are all from the Palaearctic Region ( Goetghebuer 1933 , 1938 ; Serra­
Tosio 1981 ;
Ashe & Cranston 1990 ;
Sasa & Arakawa 1994 ;
Sasa 1996 ;
Saether et al . 2000 ).

